  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "As to perceived persuasiveness, the mean values show that the propaganda campaigns were considered more persuasive when accessed through Botlitica: The mean value for the TG amounts to 51.4, while the mean value for the CG to 40.8, while the standard deviations are similar (22.6 vs 26.2), suggesting that the trend is shared across participants.",
    "This is not surprising: Conversational interfaces resulted to be more persuasive than mediated ones (e. g., text-based) in experiments held across domains since the human-likeness induced by the conversational format increases the trust level (Schulman & Bickmore, 2009).",
    "Furthermore, it is reasonable to assume that the turn-taking format nudges the journalist to keep up with the conversation rather than taking time to reflect upon fallacious rhetorical aspects of a message.",
    "These results suggest that propaganda strategies communicated through chatbots might be more effective in persuading the public, calling for the need for critical thinking of the role played by generative-AI fuelled agents implemented in the future.",
    "Zooming into the 3 forms of strategic manoeuvring the rates of perceived persuasiveness are presented in Table 2 and 3."
  ],
